				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you're really serious about making the ultimate graphics/level editor, I'll happily write you a big list of suggestions for features and overall design philosophy. :)
<br />
<br />However, if you just need something that works decently, I would recommend you to use <a href="http://members.aol.com/opentume/" class="postlink">Open tUME</a> instead. 
<br />
<br />It's main drawback that I see is that it only supports grid backgrounds, and thus you can't easily include sprites in your level design. And of course the fact that it only runs in DOS at low-resolution. 
<br />
<br />But depending on your project, these drawbacks may or may not matter to you. Developing grand tools for a project often results in having no time for the project itself. So before starting, you should ask yourself if the gain compared to using an existing tool is really worth the effort.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

